info.name: Dusk API Docs
info.description: This a collection of public APIs used to interact with nodes on the Dusk network.

item.name: Node & Network Info

request.description:
Retrieves information about the node's version, address of bootstrapping nodes, chain ID, Kadcast address and other node configuration info.

The request must be a POST request, not a GET, otherwise an invalid session ID error will be returned.

Retrieves geographic information about the location of the node's peers including country, longitute, latitude, country code.

The request must be a POST request, not a GET, otherwise an invalid session ID error will be returned.

request.description:
Retrieves a list of Kadcast addresses of the first `n` peers of the node.

The request must be a POST request, not a GET, otherwise an invalid session ID error will be returned.

The body of the POST request must contain a non-negative integer which will be the max number of peer addresses returned.

response.name: Cannot Parse Integer From Empty String
response.body: cannot parse integer from empty string

request.description:
Retrieves information about the network provisioners, their staked amounts, faults, rewards, locked amounts and owner info.

The request must be a POST request, not a GET, otherwise an invalid session ID error will be returned.
Retrieves the Common Reference String (CRS).

item.description: These endpoints can be used to retrieve general information about the network and nodes.

item.name: Ledger & Historical Info (GraphQL)

request.description: Retrieves the graphQL schema.

response.name: Successful Response
response.body:
type Block {
	header: Header!
	transactions: [SpentTransaction!]!
	reward: Int!
	fees: Int!
	gasSpent: Int!
}

type BlockPair {
	json: JSON!
}


type CallData {
	contractId: String!
	fnName: String!
	data: String!
}

type ContractEvents {
	json: JSON!
}


type Header {
	version: Int!
	height: Int!
	prevBlockHash: String!
	timestamp: Int!
	hash: String!
	stateHash: String!
	generatorBlsPubkey: String!
	txRoot: String!
	gasLimit: Int!
	seed: String!
	iteration: Int!
	json: String!
}



"""
A scalar that can represent any JSON value.
"""
scalar JSON

type MoonlightTransfers {
	json: JSON!
}

type Query {
	block(height: Float, hash: String): Block
	tx(hash: String!): SpentTransaction
	transactions(last: Int!): [SpentTransaction!]!
	blockTxs(last: Int, range: [Int!], contract: String): [SpentTransaction!]!
	blocks(last: Int, range: [Int!]): [Block!]!
	mempoolTxs: [Transaction!]!
	mempoolTx(hash: String!): Transaction
	"""
	Get a pair of two tuples containing the height and hash of the last
	block and the last finalized block.
	"""
	lastBlockPair: BlockPair!
	"""
	Retrieves the events of all historical transactions that have been
	affecting the moonlight balance of the given address.
	"""
	fullMoonlightHistory(address: String!, ord: String): MoonlightTransfers
	"""
	Retrieves raw events from transactions where at least one event within a
	transaction indicates a transfer of funds.
	
	Filter by topic="moonlight" and target=TRANSFER_CONTRACT on events for a
	tx, to get only events from moonlight transactions. (Instead of both
	phoenix or moonlight transactions)
	"""
	moonlightHistory(sender: String, receiver: String, fromBlock: Int, toBlock: Int, maxCount: Int, pageCount: Int): MoonlightTransfers
	transactionsByMemo(memo: String!): MoonlightTransfers
	"""
	Get contract events by block height or hash.
	"""
	contractEvents(height: Int, hash: String): ContractEvents
	"""
	Get all finalized contract events from a specific contract id.
	"""
	finalizedEvents(contractId: String!): ContractEvents
	"""
	Check if a given block height matches a given block hash.
	
	If `only_finalized` is set to `true`, only finalized blocks will be
	checked `only_finalized` is set to `false` by default.
	"""
	checkBlock(height: Int!, hash: String!, onlyFinalized: Boolean): Boolean!
	"""
	Get the next block height that contains a Phoenix event after the given
	block height.
	"""
	nextPhoenix(height: Int!): Int
}

type SpentTransaction {
	tx: Transaction!
	err: String
	gasSpent: Int!
	blockHash: String!
	blockHeight: Int!
	blockTimestamp: Int!
	id: String!
	raw: String!
}


type Transaction {
	raw: String!
	json: String!
	id: String!
	gasLimit: Int!
	gasPrice: Int!
	txType: String!
	callData: CallData
	isDeploy: Boolean!
	memo: String
}

schema {
	query: Query
}

request.description: Retrieves the details of a transaction identified by its hash.

}

request.description:
Retrieves the history of all transactions involving the specified moonlight address.

The history is in ascending order of block height by default. The `ord` parameter can be set to 'desc' to reverse the order.

response.name: Full Moonlight History
Full Moonligh History in Descending Order

request.description:
Retrieves the transactions inside a block.

The `last` parameter is an integer that can be used to get transactions in the latest `last` number of specified blocks. The transactions will be listed in order of descending block height.

The `range` parameter can be used to specify an inclusive range of blocks \[`from`, `to`\] whose transactions will be retrieved.

Either `last` or `range` must be specified, but not both.

A `contract` parameter which is a contract ID can optionally be specified to include only transactions that were made with the specified contract.
Retrieves a pair of two tuples containing the height and hash of the last block and the last finalized block.
Get all transactions in the mempool.

Check if a given block height matches the block hash.

An optional parameter `onlyFinalized` can be set to `true` to check only finalized blocks.
Retrieves the height of the next block that contains a phoenix event after the block height specified.
Retrieves all finalized events from a given contract ID.
Retrieves contract events by block height or hash.
Retrieves events of moonlight transactions with the specified memo.
Retrieves information of either the last `last` blocks or all blocks in an inclusive range `range`.

body.raw:
query {
    blocks(last: 20) {
        header {

item.description: Information about transactions, blocks, transaction histories and other related info can be retrieved through the graphQL endpoint `/on/graphql/query`.

item.name: Gas & Fees

request.description:
Calculates the average, maximum, minimum and median prices of the first `max_transactions` transactions with the highest gas prices in the mempool.

`max_transactions` is a non-negative integer that may be in the body of the request. If it's absent, a very large number will be used as the default.

The request must be a POST, otherwise an invalid session ID error will be returned.

Simulates a transaction to estimate the gas required to execute it.

The body of the request must be a hex-encoded transaction with '0x' prepended to the data.

For example, if the hex-encoded transaction is '01f900000000000000008621098...', then the request body must be '0x01f900000000000000008621098...'.

#### Returns

``` json
{
  "gas-spent": <gas spent during execution of transaction>,
  "error": <any error encountered while executing transaction>
}

 ```

#### Errors

- If the transaction wasn't properly hex-encoded, an `Invalid transaction` error will be returned.
    
- If the transaction's gas limit is higher than the block gas limit of 3,000,000,000, then a `Gas limit is too high` response will be returned.

item.name: Transaction Operations

request.description:
Does checks on the transaction to verify that it is valid.

The body of the request must be a hex-encoded transaction with '0x' prepended to the data.

For example, if the hex-encoded transaction is '01f900000000000000008621098...', then the request body must be '0x01f900000000000000008621098...'.

#### Returns

Does not return anything on a successful verification.

#### Errors

- If the transaction wasn't properly hex-encoded, an `Invalid Data` error will be returned.
    
- If any of the checks fail, an error is returned `Tx not accepted:`

Broadcasts a transaction to other nodes on the network.

The body of the request must be a hex-encoded transaction with '0x' prepended to the data.

For example, if the hex-encoded transaction is '01f900000000000000008621098...', then the request body must be '0x01f900000000000000008621098...'.

#### Returns

Does not return anything on a successful broadcast.

#### Errors

- If the transaction wasn't properly hex-encoded, an `Invalid Data` error will be returned.

Computes a ZK proof of the given shielded transaction.

The body of the request must contain a hex-encoded shielded transaction proof input with '0x' prepended. For example, if the input is '010000000000000017...', then the value in the body should be '0x010000000000000017...'.
